Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.80,0:00:05.33,English1,,0,0,0,,This is a story about you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.37,0:00:08.54,English1,,0,0,0,,and me and your dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:17.48,English1,,0,0,0,,There was a time not long ago... before dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.51,0:00:19.15,English1,,0,0,0,,They didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.18,0:00:22.62,English1,,0,0,0,,Now there are big ones, small ones, snugglers,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.65,0:00:24.18,English1,,0,0,0,,guardians, hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.22,0:00:26.79,English1,,0,0,0,,Every kind of dog you could possibly want.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.82,0:00:29.36,English1,,0,0,0,,How did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.39,0:00:30.66,English1,,0,0,0,,It's not just dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.69,0:00:31.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Where did all the different kinds
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.93,0:00:34.66,English1,,0,0,0,,of living creatures come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.70,0:00:39.03,English1,,0,0,0,,The answer is a transforming\Npower that sounds like something
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.07,0:00:41.67,English1,,0,0,0,,straight out of a fairy tale or myth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.70,0:00:43.80,English1,,0,0,0,,but it's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.93,0:02:20.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Let's go back across 30,000\Nyears to a time before dogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.84,0:02:23.97,English1,,0,0,0,,when our ancestors lived in the endless winter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.01,0:02:25.97,English1,,0,0,0,,of the last ice age.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.01,0:02:29.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Our ancestors were wanderers\Nliving in small bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.54,0:02:31.81,English1,,0,0,0,,They slept beneath the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.85,0:02:35.12,English1,,0,0,0,,The sky was their storybook, calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.15,0:02:38.12,English1,,0,0,0,,an instruction manual for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.15,0:02:40.82,English1,,0,0,0,,It told them when the bitter colds would come,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.86,0:02:42.82,English1,,0,0,0,,when the wild grains would ripen,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.86,0:02:46.43,English1,,0,0,0,,when the herds of caribou\Nand bison would be on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.46,0:02:50.43,English1,,0,0,0,,Their idea of home was Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.46,0:02:54.17,English1,,0,0,0,,But they lived in fear of other hungry creatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.20,0:02:56.30,English1,,0,0,0,,the mountain lions and the bears
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.34,0:02:58.94,English1,,0,0,0,,that competed with them for the same prey
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:03:01.71,English1,,0,0,0,,and the wolves that threatened to carry off and devour
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.74,0:03:03.91,English1,,0,0,0,,the most vulnerable among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.10,0:03:24.03,English1,,0,0,0,,All the wolves want to get at the bone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:26.63,English1,,0,0,0,,but most of them are too\Nfrightened to come close enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.67,0:03:29.14,English1,,0,0,0,,Their fear is due to high levels
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.17,0:03:30.97,English1,,0,0,0,,of stress hormones in their blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.01,0:03:32.87,English1,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:35.58,English1,,0,0,0,,Because coming too close to humans can be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:38.88,English1,,0,0,0,,But a few wolves-- due to natural variations--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.91,0:03:40.68,English1,,0,0,0,,have lower levels of those hormones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.72,0:03:43.62,English1,,0,0,0,,This makes them less afraid of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.06,0:03:49.49,English1,,0,0,0,,This wolf has discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:51.16,English1,,0,0,0,,what a branch of his ancestors figured out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.19,0:03:53.16,English1,,0,0,0,,some 15,000 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.19,0:03:56.16,English1,,0,0,0,,an excellent survival strategy;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.20,0:03:59.43,English1,,0,0,0,,the domestication of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.47,0:04:03.00,English1,,0,0,0,,Let the humans do the hunting,\Ndon't threaten them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.04,0:04:05.01,English1,,0,0,0,,and they'll let you scavenge their garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.04,0:04:08.21,English1,,0,0,0,,You'll eat more regularly,\Nyou'll leave more offspring,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.24,0:04:11.04,English1,,0,0,0,,and those offspring will inherit your disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.08,0:04:14.45,English1,,0,0,0,,This selection for tameness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.58,English1,,0,0,0,,would be reinforced with each generation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.62,0:04:21.42,English1,,0,0,0,,until that line of wild wolves evolves into...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.46,0:04:23.52,English1,,0,0,0,,dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.56,0:04:26.56,English1,,0,0,0,,You might call this "survival of the friendliest."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:34.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Then as now, this was a good\Ndeal for the humans, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.24,0:04:37.54,English1,,0,0,0,,The scavenging dogs weren't just a sanitation squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.57,0:04:39.37,English1,,0,0,0,,They worked security.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.79,0:04:58.12,English1,,0,0,0,,As this interspecies partnership\Ncontinued over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:01.83,English1,,0,0,0,,the dogs' appearance changed also.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.86,0:05:04.10,English1,,0,0,0,,Cuteness became a selective advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.13,0:05:06.63,English1,,0,0,0,,The more adorable you were,\Nthe better chance you had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.67,0:05:10.07,English1,,0,0,0,,to live and pass on your genes\Nto another generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.10,0:05:12.07,English1,,0,0,0,,What began as an alliance of convenience
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:16.34,English1,,0,0,0,,became a friendship that deepened over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:17.98,English1,,0,0,0,,To see what happens next,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.01,0:05:20.45,English1,,0,0,0,,let's leave our distant ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.48,0:05:24.75,English1,,0,0,0,,of some 20,000 years ago to visit the more recent past
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.79,0:05:27.62,English1,,0,0,0,,during an intermission in the Ice Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:31.42,English1,,0,0,0,,This break in the climate starts a revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.46,0:05:35.10,English1,,0,0,0,,Instead of wandering, people are settling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.13,0:05:39.03,English1,,0,0,0,,There's something new in the world... villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.07,0:05:40.77,English1,,0,0,0,,People still hunt and gather,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.80,0:05:44.44,English1,,0,0,0,,but now they also produce food and clothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.47,0:05:45.97,English1,,0,0,0,,agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.68,0:05:53.95,English1,,0,0,0,,The wolves have traded their freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:56.38,English1,,0,0,0,,in exchange for a steady meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.42,0:05:59.15,English1,,0,0,0,,They've given up their right to choose a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.19,0:06:02.19,English1,,0,0,0,,Now the humans choose for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.22,0:06:06.29,English1,,0,0,0,,They consistently kill off\N{\i1}the dogs that can't be trained;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.33,0:06:07.99,English1,,0,0,0,,the ones that bite the feeding hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.03,0:06:12.23,English1,,0,0,0,,And they breed the dogs that please them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:18.37,English1,,0,0,0,,They nurture those dogs that do their bidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.41,0:06:21.58,English1,,0,0,0,,hunting, herding, guarding, hauling,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.61,0:06:22.68,English1,,0,0,0,,and keeping them company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.71,0:06:24.31,English1,,0,0,0,,From every litter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:27.31,English1,,0,0,0,,the humans select the puppies they like best.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.35,0:06:29.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Over the generations, the dogs evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:34.22,English1,,0,0,0,,This kind of evolution is called "artificial selection"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:35.76,English1,,0,0,0,,or "breeding."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.79,0:06:38.02,English1,,0,0,0,,Turning wolves into dogs was\N{\i1}the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.06,0:06:41.19,English1,,0,0,0,,we humans took evolution into our own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.33,English1,,0,0,0,,And we've been doing it ever since
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:47.43,English1,,0,0,0,,to shape all the plants\N{\i1}and animals that we depend on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.47,0:06:51.61,English1,,0,0,0,,In a blink of cosmic time,\N{\i1}just 15,000 or 20,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:55.04,English1,,0,0,0,,we turned gray wolves into all the kinds of dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.08,0:06:56.41,English1,,0,0,0,,we love today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.44,0:06:57.94,English1,,0,0,0,,Think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:06:59.95,English1,,0,0,0,,Every breed of dog you've ever seen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:02.75,English1,,0,0,0,,was sculpted by human hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.78,0:07:06.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Many of our best friends--\N{\i1}the most popular breeds--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.29,0:07:08.89,English1,,0,0,0,,were created in only the last few centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.79,0:07:13.86,English1,,0,0,0,,The awesome power of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:15.46,English1,,0,0,0,,transformed the ravenous wolf
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:18.10,English1,,0,0,0,,into the faithful shepherd...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.13,0:07:21.97,English1,,0,0,0,,...who protects the herd and drives the wolf away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.82,0:07:39.12,English1,,0,0,0,,Artificial selection turned\Nthe wolf into the shepherd
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.15,0:07:42.06,English1,,0,0,0,,and the wild grasses into wheat and corn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.09,0:07:45.59,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, almost every plant\Nand animal that we eat today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:49.30,English1,,0,0,0,,was bred from a wild, less-edible ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:52.93,English1,,0,0,0,,If artificial selection can work such profound changes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.97,0:07:55.67,English1,,0,0,0,,in only 10,000 or 15,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:57.84,English1,,0,0,0,,what can natural selection do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:00.61,English1,,0,0,0,,operating over billions of years?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:05.91,English1,,0,0,0,,The answer is all the beauty and diversity of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:07.85,English1,,0,0,0,,How does it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:12.95,English1,,0,0,0,,Our Ship of the Imagination\N{\i1}can take us anywhere in space
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:16.62,English1,,0,0,0,,and time, even to the hidden microcosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.66,0:08:20.66,English1,,0,0,0,,where one kind of life can be\N{\i1}transformed into another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.70,0:08:22.63,English1,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:31.36,English1,,0,0,0,,May not seem like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:33.26,English1,,0,0,0,,but we've been living in an ice age
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.29,0:08:35.03,English1,,0,0,0,,for the last two million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.06,0:08:37.60,English1,,0,0,0,,This just happens to be\None of the long intermissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.63,0:08:39.40,English1,,0,0,0,,For most of those two million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.43,0:08:41.90,English1,,0,0,0,,the climate has been cold and dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.94,0:08:44.64,English1,,0,0,0,,The North Polar ice cap extended much farther south
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:46.81,English1,,0,0,0,,than it does today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.84,0:08:50.21,English1,,0,0,0,,In one of those long, cold glacial periods
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:53.11,English1,,0,0,0,,when the winter sea ice\Nstretched from the North Pole
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:55.62,English1,,0,0,0,,all the way down to what is now Los Angeles,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.65,0:09:00.35,English1,,0,0,0,,great bears roamed the frozen\N{\i1}wastes of Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.96,0:09:08.73,English1,,0,0,0,,This might look like an ordinary bear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:12.07,English1,,0,0,0,,but something extraordinary\N{\i1}is happening inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:15.57,English1,,0,0,0,,Something that will give rise\Nto a new species.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:17.24,English1,,0,0,0,,In order to see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.27,0:09:20.61,English1,,0,0,0,,we'll need to descend down\Nto a much smaller scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.58,English1,,0,0,0,,to the cellular level,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.61,0:09:26.85,English1,,0,0,0,,so that we can explore\N{\i1}the bear's reproductive system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.35,0:09:34.55,English1,,0,0,0,,We'll take the subclavian artery through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:58.88,English1,,0,0,0,,Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:06.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Those are some of her eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.92,0:10:09.46,English1,,0,0,0,,To see what's going on in one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:11.36,English1,,0,0,0,,we'll have to get even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.39,0:10:14.76,English1,,0,0,0,,We'll have to shrink down to the molecular level.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.36,0:10:20.40,English1,,0,0,0,,Our Ship of the Imagination is now so small,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:24.34,English1,,0,0,0,,you could fit a million of them into a grain of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.37,0:10:28.31,English1,,0,0,0,,See those guys over there\Nstrutting along those girders?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.34,0:10:31.58,English1,,0,0,0,,They are proteins\Ncalled kinesin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:34.31,English1,,0,0,0,,These kinesin are part of the transport crew
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.35,0:10:37.15,English1,,0,0,0,,that's busy moving cargo around the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.18,0:10:39.02,English1,,0,0,0,,How alien they seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.05,0:10:42.82,English1,,0,0,0,,And yet these tiny creatures--\Nand beings like them--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.86,0:10:47.56,English1,,0,0,0,,are a part of every living cell,\Nincluding the ones inside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:52.20,English1,,0,0,0,,If life has a sanctuary,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.23,0:10:56.07,English1,,0,0,0,,it's here in the nucleus\Nwhich contains our DNA...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.10,0:10:59.77,English1,,0,0,0,,the ancient scripture\Nof our genetic code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.81,0:11:04.91,English1,,0,0,0,,And it's written in a language\Nthat all life can read.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.39,0:11:15.09,English1,,0,0,0,,DNA is a molecule shaped\N{\i1}like a long twisted ladder
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:17.26,English1,,0,0,0,,or double helix.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.29,0:11:19.06,English1,,0,0,0,,The rungs of the ladder are made
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.09,0:11:21.39,English1,,0,0,0,,of four different kinds of smaller molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:24.40,English1,,0,0,0,,These are the letters of the genetic alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:27.37,English1,,0,0,0,,Particular arrangements of those letters spell out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.80,English1,,0,0,0,,the instructions for all living things,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.84,0:11:33.24,English1,,0,0,0,,telling them how to grow, move, digest,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:36.74,English1,,0,0,0,,sense the environment, heal, reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:39.91,English1,,0,0,0,,The DNA double helix is a molecular machine
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.95,0:11:43.98,English1,,0,0,0,,with about 100 billion parts called "atoms."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:47.59,English1,,0,0,0,,There are as many atoms\Nin a single molecule of your DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.62,0:11:51.39,English1,,0,0,0,,as there are stars in a typical galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.43,0:11:53.49,English1,,0,0,0,,The same is true for dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.53,0:11:56.10,English1,,0,0,0,,and bears
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.13,0:11:59.57,English1,,0,0,0,,and every living thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:03.87,English1,,0,0,0,,We are, each of us, a little universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.38,0:12:15.28,English1,,0,0,0,,The DNA message handed down from cell to cell
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:17.42,English1,,0,0,0,,and from generation to generation is copied
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.45,0:12:19.15,English1,,0,0,0,,with extreme care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.19,0:12:23.76,English1,,0,0,0,,The birth of a new DNA molecule\Nbegins when an unwinding protein
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:26.26,English1,,0,0,0,,separates the two strands of the double helix,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.29,0:12:28.16,English1,,0,0,0,,breaking the rungs apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.20,0:12:30.50,English1,,0,0,0,,Inside the liquid of the nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.53,0:12:34.43,English1,,0,0,0,,the molecular letters of\Nthe genetic code float freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:37.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Each strand of the helix copies its lost partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.87,0:12:40.84,English1,,0,0,0,,resulting in two identical DNA molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:43.88,English1,,0,0,0,,That's how life reproduces genes and transmits them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.91,0:12:45.95,English1,,0,0,0,,from one generation to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.98,0:12:48.55,English1,,0,0,0,,When a living cell divides in two,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:53.05,English1,,0,0,0,,each one takes away with it\N{\i1}a complete copy of the DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.09,0:12:56.82,English1,,0,0,0,,A specialized protein proofreads to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.86,0:12:58.66,English1,,0,0,0,,that only the right letters are accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.69,0:13:01.53,English1,,0,0,0,,so that the DNA is accurately copied.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.56,0:13:03.30,English1,,0,0,0,,But nobody's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.33,0:13:06.50,English1,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, a proofreading error slips through,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.53,0:13:10.30,English1,,0,0,0,,making a small, random change in the genetic instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.34,0:13:13.54,English1,,0,0,0,,A mutation has occurred in the bear's egg cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.57,0:13:17.48,English1,,0,0,0,,A random event as tiny as\N{\i1}this one can have consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:19.75,English1,,0,0,0,,on a far grander scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:26.59,English1,,0,0,0,,That mutation altered the gene\N{\i1}that controls fur color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:29.59,English1,,0,0,0,,It will affect the production of dark pigment in the fur
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.62,0:13:31.59,English1,,0,0,0,,of the bear's offspring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:33.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Most mutations are harmless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:35.66,English1,,0,0,0,,Some are deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.70,0:13:38.57,English1,,0,0,0,,But a few, purely by chance,\N{\i1}can give an organism
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.60,0:13:42.27,English1,,0,0,0,,a critical advantage over the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:44.27,English1,,0,0,0,,A year has passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.31,0:13:46.11,English1,,0,0,0,,Our bear is now a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.14,0:13:47.84,English1,,0,0,0,,And as a result of that mutation,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:51.51,English1,,0,0,0,,one of her two cubs was born with a white coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:54.25,English1,,0,0,0,,When the cubs get old enough\N{\i1}to venture out on their own,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.28,0:13:56.55,English1,,0,0,0,,which bear is more likely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:14:00.75,English1,,0,0,0,,to be able to sneak up on unsuspecting prey?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:04.02,English1,,0,0,0,,The brown bear can be seen against the snow a mile away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.06,0:14:06.93,English1,,0,0,0,,The white bear prospers and passes on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:08.90,English1,,0,0,0,,its own particular set of genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:11.76,English1,,0,0,0,,This happens repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:13.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Over succeeding generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.97,0:14:16.54,English1,,0,0,0,,the gene for white fur spreads through
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.57,0:14:19.21,English1,,0,0,0,,the entire population of Arctic bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:21.94,English1,,0,0,0,,The gene for dark fur loses out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.98,0:14:24.74,English1,,0,0,0,,in the competition for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.75,0:14:30.62,English1,,0,0,0,,Mutations are entirely random and happen all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:32.59,English1,,0,0,0,,But the environment rewards those
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:34.89,English1,,0,0,0,,that increase the chance for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.92,0:14:37.29,English1,,0,0,0,,It naturally selects the living things
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.32,0:14:39.96,English1,,0,0,0,,that are better suited to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.99,0:14:42.80,English1,,0,0,0,,And that selection is the opposite of random.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:48.10,English1,,0,0,0,,The two populations of bears separated,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.14,0:14:49.97,English1,,0,0,0,,and over thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:53.14,English1,,0,0,0,,evolved other characteristics that set them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.17,0:14:56.38,English1,,0,0,0,,They became different species.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:00.85,English1,,0,0,0,,That's what Charles Darwin meant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.88,0:15:04.52,English1,,0,0,0,,by "the origin of species."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.55,0:15:07.09,English1,,0,0,0,,An individual{\i1} bear doesn't evolve;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:11.02,English1,,0,0,0,,the population{\i1} of bears evolves over generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:14.79,English1,,0,0,0,,If the Arctic ice continues to dwindle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:18.50,English1,,0,0,0,,due to global warming, the polar bears may go extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.53,0:15:20.53,English1,,0,0,0,,They'll be replaced by brown bears,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.57,0:15:23.70,English1,,0,0,0,,better adapted to the now defrosted environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:28.21,English1,,0,0,0,,This is a different story from the one about the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:30.71,English1,,0,0,0,,No breeder guided these changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:34.21,English1,,0,0,0,,Instead, the environment itself selects them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.25,0:15:36.88,English1,,0,0,0,,This is evolution by natural selection,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:40.69,English1,,0,0,0,,the most revolutionary concept in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:44.86,English1,,0,0,0,,Darwin first presented the evidence for this idea in 1859.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.89,0:15:48.90,English1,,0,0,0,,The uproar it caused has never subsided.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.93,0:15:50.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.23,0:16:00.33,English1,,0,0,0,,We all understand the twinge of discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.36,0:16:03.60,English1,,0,0,0,,at the thought that we share a common ancestor with the apes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.63,0:16:06.97,English1,,0,0,0,,No one can embarrass you like a relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:09.17,English1,,0,0,0,,Our closest ones, the chimpanzees,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.20,0:16:11.84,English1,,0,0,0,,they frequently behave inappropriately in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:14.11,English1,,0,0,0,,There's an understandable human need
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:16.34,English1,,0,0,0,,to distance ourselves from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:18.61,English1,,0,0,0,,A central premise of traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.65,0:16:20.61,English1,,0,0,0,,is that we were created separately
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.65,0:16:22.62,English1,,0,0,0,,from all the other animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.65,0:16:25.39,English1,,0,0,0,,It's easy to see why this idea has taken hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:28.22,English1,,0,0,0,,It makes us feel... special.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.26,0:16:32.33,English1,,0,0,0,,But what about our kinship with the trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:34.76,English1,,0,0,0,,How does that make you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.44,0:16:45.67,English1,,0,0,0,,Okay, here's a segment of the oak tree's DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.71,0:16:47.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Think of it like a bar code.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.88,0:16:50.48,English1,,0,0,0,,The instructions written in the code of life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:53.48,English1,,0,0,0,,tell the tree how to metabolize sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.51,0:16:56.78,English1,,0,0,0,,Now let's compare it with the same section of my own DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.02,0:17:03.92,English1,,0,0,0,,The DNA doesn't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.96,0:17:07.26,English1,,0,0,0,,This tree and me-- we're long-lost cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:09.26,English1,,0,0,0,,And it's not just the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.30,0:17:12.17,English1,,0,0,0,,If you go back far enough, you'll find that we share
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.20,0:17:14.20,English1,,0,0,0,,a common ancestor with...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:15.54,English1,,0,0,0,,the butterfly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.57,0:17:17.17,English1,,0,0,0,,gray wolf...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:18.57,English1,,0,0,0,,mushroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.61,0:17:20.21,English1,,0,0,0,,shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:21.67,English1,,0,0,0,,bacterium...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.71,0:17:23.01,English1,,0,0,0,,sparrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.04,0:17:24.58,English1,,0,0,0,,What a family!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.61,0:17:28.11,English1,,0,0,0,,Other parts of the bar code vary\Nfrom species to species.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:31.35,English1,,0,0,0,,That's what makes the difference\Nbetween an owl and an octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.39,0:17:33.59,English1,,0,0,0,,Unless you have an identical twin,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:35.89,English1,,0,0,0,,there's no one else in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.92,0:17:38.56,English1,,0,0,0,,with the exact same DNA as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.59,0:17:40.79,English1,,0,0,0,,Within other species, the genetic differences
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:44.20,English1,,0,0,0,,provide the raw material for natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.23,0:17:48.13,English1,,0,0,0,,The environment selects which genes survive and multiply.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.17,0:17:50.30,English1,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the genetic instructions for life's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:52.31,English1,,0,0,0,,most basic functions--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.34,0:17:55.11,English1,,0,0,0,,say, digesting sugars-- we and other species
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.14,0:17:57.14,English1,,0,0,0,,are almost identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:18:00.28,English1,,0,0,0,,That's because those functions are so basic to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:03.22,English1,,0,0,0,,they evolved before the various life-forms
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.25,0:18:05.22,English1,,0,0,0,,branched off from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.25,0:18:07.69,English1,,0,0,0,,This is our Tree of Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:09.22,English1,,0,0,0,,Science has made it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.26,0:18:11.39,English1,,0,0,0,,for us to construct this family tree
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.43,0:18:13.39,English1,,0,0,0,,for all the species of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.43,0:18:17.23,English1,,0,0,0,,Close genetic relatives occupy\N{\i1}the same branch of the tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.26,0:18:20.87,English1,,0,0,0,,while more distant cousins are farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:23.07,English1,,0,0,0,,Each twig is a living species.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.07,0:18:28.24,English1,,0,0,0,,And the trunk of the tree\N{\i1}represents the common ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.28,0:18:31.08,English1,,0,0,0,,of all life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:33.48,English1,,0,0,0,,The stuff of life is so malleable
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.51,0:18:36.45,English1,,0,0,0,,that once it got started,\N{\i1}the environment molded it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:39.75,English1,,0,0,0,,into a staggering variety of forms--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.79,0:18:43.59,English1,,0,0,0,,10,000 times more than we can possibly show here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.59,0:18:47.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Biologists have catalogued
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:51.26,English1,,0,0,0,,a half a million different kinds of beetles alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.97,0:18:56.57,English1,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the numberless varieties
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:18:58.24,English1,,0,0,0,,of bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.27,0:19:00.61,English1,,0,0,0,,There are many millions of living species
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:03.01,English1,,0,0,0,,of animals and plants,  most of them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:05.41,English1,,0,0,0,,still unknown to science.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.45,0:19:08.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Think of that--\N{\i1}we have yet to make contact
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.55,0:19:11.85,English1,,0,0,0,,with most of the forms of terrestrial life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:14.29,English1,,0,0,0,,That's how many kinds of life there are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:16.06,English1,,0,0,0,,on this tiny planet alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.06,0:19:20.59,English1,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Life extends its feelers in all directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.63,0:19:22.20,English1,,0,0,0,,finding and exploiting what works,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.23,0:19:23.93,English1,,0,0,0,,creating new environments
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.96,0:19:26.20,English1,,0,0,0,,and opportunities for new forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.37,0:19:33.11,English1,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Life is three and a half billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.14,0:19:35.31,English1,,0,0,0,,That's plenty of time to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:38.51,English1,,0,0,0,,an impressive repertoire of tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.92,0:19:43.55,English1,,0,0,0,,Evolution can disguise an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.58,0:19:46.02,English1,,0,0,0,,as a plant...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.52,0:19:52.49,English1,,0,0,0,,...taking thousands of generations
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:55.66,English1,,0,0,0,,to contrive an elaborate costume
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.70,0:19:57.56,English1,,0,0,0,,that fools predators into looking elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:20:00.07,English1,,0,0,0,,for someone to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:04.07,English1,,0,0,0,,Or it can disguise a plant as an animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.10,0:20:07.21,English1,,0,0,0,,evolving blossoms that take on\N{\i1}the appearance of a wasp--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:11.24,English1,,0,0,0,,the orchid's way of fooling real wasps into pollinating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.28,0:20:14.35,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:17.78,English1,,0,0,0,,shape-shifting power of natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:29.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Among the dense, tangled limbs of the vast Tree of Life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.23,0:20:31.36,English1,,0,0,0,,you are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.40,0:20:35.67,English1,,0,0,0,,One tiny branch among countless millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.70,0:20:40.71,English1,,0,0,0,,Science reveals that all life on Earth is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.38,0:20:46.55,English1,,0,0,0,,Darwin discovered the actual mechanis of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.58,0:20:49.58,English1,,0,0,0,,The prevailing belief was that the complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:52.25,English1,,0,0,0,,and variety of life must be the work
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.29,0:20:55.22,English1,,0,0,0,,of an intelligent designer, who created each
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.26,0:20:58.39,English1,,0,0,0,,of these millions of different species separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.43,0:21:01.90,English1,,0,0,0,,Living things are just too intricate, it was said,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:05.47,English1,,0,0,0,,to be the result of unguided evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:07.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Consider the human eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.97,0:21:10.20,English1,,0,0,0,,a masterpiece of complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.87,0:21:15.98,English1,,0,0,0,,It requires a cornea,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.01,0:21:19.45,English1,,0,0,0,,iris, lens, retina,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.48,0:21:21.85,English1,,0,0,0,,optic nerves, muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:24.58,English1,,0,0,0,,let alone the brain's elaborate neural network
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.62,0:21:27.52,English1,,0,0,0,,to interpret images.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.56,0:21:30.42,English1,,0,0,0,,It's more complicated than any device
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.46,0:21:33.53,English1,,0,0,0,,ever crafted by human intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:35.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it was argued,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.23,0:21:37.26,English1,,0,0,0,,the human eye can't be the result
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.30,0:21:39.60,English1,,0,0,0,,of mindless evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:43.64,English1,,0,0,0,,To know if that's true,\N{\i1}we need to travel across time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.67,0:21:47.31,English1,,0,0,0,,to a world before there were eyes to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.82,0:22:06.38,English1,,0,0,0,,In the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.42,0:22:08.02,English1,,0,0,0,,life was blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.09,0:22:12.22,English1,,0,0,0,,This is what our world looked like
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.26,0:22:14.23,English1,,0,0,0,,four billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.26,0:22:17.90,English1,,0,0,0,,before there were any eyes to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.93,0:22:20.97,English1,,0,0,0,,Until a few hundred million years passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.00,0:22:22.60,English1,,0,0,0,,and then, one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.63,0:22:24.67,English1,,0,0,0,,there was a microscopic copying error
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.70,0:22:26.24,English1,,0,0,0,,in the DNA of a bacterium.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.27,0:22:28.97,English1,,0,0,0,,This random mutation gave that microbe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.01,0:22:31.78,English1,,0,0,0,,a protein molecule that absorbed sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.81,0:22:33.61,English1,,0,0,0,,Want to know what the world looked like
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.65,0:22:35.31,English1,,0,0,0,,to a light-sensitive bacterium?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.35,0:22:38.62,English1,,0,0,0,,Take a look at the right side of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.65,0:22:42.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Mutations continued to occur at random,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.29,0:22:45.52,English1,,0,0,0,,as they always do in any\N{\i1}population of living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.53,0:22:49.63,English1,,0,0,0,,Another mutation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:53.60,English1,,0,0,0,,caused a dark bacterium to flee intense light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.63,0:22:56.00,English1,,0,0,0,,What is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.03,0:22:57.77,English1,,0,0,0,,Night and day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.80,0:22:59.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Those bacteria that could tell light from dark
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.84,0:23:02.47,English1,,0,0,0,,had a decisive advantage over the ones that couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.51,0:23:04.31,English1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.34,0:23:07.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Because the daytime brought harsh, ultraviolet light
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.51,0:23:09.45,English1,,0,0,0,,that damages DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.48,0:23:13.02,English1,,0,0,0,,The sensitive bacteria fled the intense light
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:15.55,English1,,0,0,0,,to safely exchange their DNA in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.59,0:23:17.49,English1,,0,0,0,,They survived in greater numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.52,0:23:19.96,English1,,0,0,0,,than the bacteria that stayed at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.99,0:23:23.06,English1,,0,0,0,,Over time, those light-sensitive proteins
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.10,0:23:25.70,English1,,0,0,0,,became concentrated in a pigment spot
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.73,0:23:29.00,English1,,0,0,0,,on the more advanced, one-celled organism.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.03,0:23:32.20,English1,,0,0,0,,This made it possible to find the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.24,0:23:34.34,English1,,0,0,0,,an overwhelming advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.37,0:23:37.68,English1,,0,0,0,,for an organism that harvests sunlight to make food.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.78,0:23:47.69,English1,,0,0,0,,Here's a flatworm's-eye view of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.72,0:23:49.85,English1,,0,0,0,,This multi-celled organism
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.89,0:23:52.19,English1,,0,0,0,,evolved a dimple in the pigment spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.22,0:23:54.49,English1,,0,0,0,,The bowl-shaped depression
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.53,0:23:57.86,English1,,0,0,0,,allowed the animal to distinguish light from shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.90,0:24:01.23,English1,,0,0,0,,to crudely make out objects in its vicinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.27,0:24:05.27,English1,,0,0,0,,including those to eat and those that might eat it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.30,0:24:07.84,English1,,0,0,0,,a tremendous advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.87,0:24:10.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Later, things became a little clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.54,0:24:12.24,English1,,0,0,0,,The dimple deepened
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.28,0:24:15.01,English1,,0,0,0,,and evolved into a socket with a small opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.05,0:24:17.38,English1,,0,0,0,,Over thousands of generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.42,0:24:20.62,English1,,0,0,0,,natural selection was slowly sculpting the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.42,0:24:25.56,English1,,0,0,0,,The opening contracted to a pinhole covered
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.59,0:24:27.89,English1,,0,0,0,,by a protective transparent membrane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.93,0:24:30.39,English1,,0,0,0,,Only a little light could enter the tiny hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.43,0:24:32.80,English1,,0,0,0,,but it was enough to paint a dim image
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.83,0:24:35.37,English1,,0,0,0,,on the sensitive inner surface of the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.40,0:24:37.27,English1,,0,0,0,,This sharpened the focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.30,0:24:39.60,English1,,0,0,0,,A larger opening would have let in more light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.64,0:24:43.21,English1,,0,0,0,,to make a brighter image but one that was out of focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.24,0:24:46.11,English1,,0,0,0,,This development launched the visual equivalent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.15,0:24:48.78,English1,,0,0,0,,of an arms race.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.19,0:25:03.76,English1,,0,0,0,,The competition needed to keep up to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.80,0:25:07.50,English1,,0,0,0,,But then a splendid new feature of the eye evolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.53,0:25:12.50,English1,,0,0,0,,a lens that provided both\N{\i1}brightness and sharp focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.54,0:25:14.94,English1,,0,0,0,,In the eyes of primitive fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.97,0:25:18.68,English1,,0,0,0,,the transparent gel near\N{\i1}the pinhole formed into a lens.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.71,0:25:21.45,English1,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the pinhole enlarged
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.48,0:25:23.51,English1,,0,0,0,,to let in more and more light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.55,0:25:25.95,English1,,0,0,0,,Fish could now see in high-def,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.98,0:25:29.69,English1,,0,0,0,,both close up and far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.72,0:25:33.32,English1,,0,0,0,,And then something terrible happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.36,0:25:36.83,English1,,0,0,0,,Have you ever noticed that a straw in a glass of water
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.86,0:25:39.33,English1,,0,0,0,,looks bent at the surface of the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.36,0:25:42.10,English1,,0,0,0,,That's because light bends when it goes from one medium
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.13,0:25:45.00,English1,,0,0,0,,to another, say from water to air.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.04,0:25:48.77,English1,,0,0,0,,Our eyes originally evolved to see in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.81,0:25:51.68,English1,,0,0,0,,The watery fluid in those eyes neatly
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.71,0:25:55.48,English1,,0,0,0,,eliminated the distortion of that bending effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.48,0:25:58.65,English1,,0,0,0,,But for land animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.68,0:26:01.05,English1,,0,0,0,,the light carries images from dry air
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.09,0:26:04.16,English1,,0,0,0,,into their still-watery eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.19,0:26:05.72,English1,,0,0,0,,That bends the light rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.76,0:26:09.73,English1,,0,0,0,,causing all kinds of distortions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.76,0:26:12.50,English1,,0,0,0,,When our amphibious ancestors left the water for the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.53,0:26:15.73,English1,,0,0,0,,their eyes, exquisitely evolved to see in water,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.77,0:26:18.07,English1,,0,0,0,,were lousy for seeing in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.10,0:26:20.74,English1,,0,0,0,,Our vision has never been as good since.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.77,0:26:23.67,English1,,0,0,0,,We like to think of our eyes as state-of-the-art,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.71,0:26:26.58,English1,,0,0,0,,but 375 million years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.61,0:26:29.01,English1,,0,0,0,,we still can't see things right in front of our noses
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.05,0:26:31.68,English1,,0,0,0,,or discern fine details in near darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.72,0:26:33.58,English1,,0,0,0,,the way fish can.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.62,0:26:35.09,English1,,0,0,0,,When we left the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.12,0:26:37.26,English1,,0,0,0,,why didn't nature just start over again
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.29,0:26:38.89,English1,,0,0,0,,and evolve us a new set of eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.92,0:26:41.23,English1,,0,0,0,,that were optimal for seeing in the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.26,0:26:43.33,English1,,0,0,0,,Nature doesn't work that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.36,0:26:46.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Evolution reshapes existing structures over generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.77,0:26:48.93,English1,,0,0,0,,adapting them with small changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.97,0:26:50.60,English1,,0,0,0,,It can't just go back to the drawing board
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.64,0:26:52.44,English1,,0,0,0,,and start from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.47,0:26:56.01,English1,,0,0,0,,At every stage of its development, the evolving eye
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.04,0:26:57.74,English1,,0,0,0,,functioned well enough
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.78,0:27:00.91,English1,,0,0,0,,to provide a selective advantage for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.95,0:27:03.78,English1,,0,0,0,,And among animals alive today,\N{\i1}we find eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.82,0:27:06.98,English1,,0,0,0,,at all these stages of development.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.26,0:27:13.56,English1,,0,0,0,,And all of them function.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.59,0:27:15.73,English1,,0,0,0,,The complexity of the human eye poses
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.76,0:27:17.86,English1,,0,0,0,,no challenge to evolution by natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.90,0:27:22.37,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, the eye and all of biology makes no sense\Nwithout evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.40,0:27:24.04,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, the eye and all of biology makes no sense\Nwithout evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.07,0:27:26.70,English1,,0,0,0,,Some claim that evolution is just a theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.74,0:27:29.91,English1,,0,0,0,,as if it were merely an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.94,0:27:32.64,English1,,0,0,0,,The theory of evolution, like the theory of gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.68,0:27:34.75,English1,,0,0,0,,is a scientific fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.78,0:27:37.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Evolution really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.52,0:27:39.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Accepting our kinship with all life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.95,0:27:41.99,English1,,0,0,0,,is not only solid science.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.02,0:27:47.19,English1,,0,0,0,,In my view, it's also a soaring spiritual experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.97,0:27:56.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Because evolution is blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.84,0:28:01.07,English1,,0,0,0,,it cannot anticipate or adapt\N{\i1}to catastrophic events.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.11,0:28:04.91,English1,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Life has some broken branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.94,0:28:08.41,English1,,0,0,0,,Many of them were severed in the five greatest catastrophes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:09.98,English1,,0,0,0,,that life has ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.32,0:28:12.28,English1,,0,0,0,,Somewhere, there's a memorial
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.32,0:28:15.29,English1,,0,0,0,,to the multitude of lost species,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.32,0:28:17.46,English1,,0,0,0,,the Halls of Extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.49,0:28:19.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.29,0:28:31.49,English1,,0,0,0,,_
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.63,0:28:34.87,English1,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the Halls of Extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.65,0:28:39.55,English1,,0,0,0,,A monument to the broken branches of the Tree of Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.46,0:28:53.16,English1,,0,0,0,,For every single one of the millions of species
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.20,0:28:57.43,English1,,0,0,0,,alive today, perhaps a thousand others have perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.47,0:28:59.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Most of them died out in the everyday competition
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.97,0:29:01.50,English1,,0,0,0,,with other life-forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.54,0:29:05.11,English1,,0,0,0,,But many of them were swept away\Nin vast cataclysms
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.14,0:29:07.34,English1,,0,0,0,,that overwhelmed the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.38,0:29:09.78,English1,,0,0,0,,In the last 500 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.81,0:29:12.48,English1,,0,0,0,,this has happened five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.52,0:29:17.69,English1,,0,0,0,,Five mass extinctions that devastated life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.72,0:29:22.96,English1,,0,0,0,,The worst one of all happened some 250 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:25.53,English1,,0,0,0,,at the end of an era
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.56,0:29:28.00,English1,,0,0,0,,known as the Permian.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.38,0:29:47.12,English1,,0,0,0,,Trilobites were armored animals that hunted
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.15,0:29:49.62,English1,,0,0,0,,in great herds across the seafloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.65,0:29:52.32,English1,,0,0,0,,They were among the first animals to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.35,0:29:54.76,English1,,0,0,0,,image-forming eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.33,0:30:01.33,English1,,0,0,0,,Trilobites had a good long run, some 270 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.36,0:30:04.90,English1,,0,0,0,,Earth was once the planet of the trilobites.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.93,0:30:08.34,English1,,0,0,0,,But now they're all gone, extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.37,0:30:11.07,English1,,0,0,0,,The last of them were swept from life's stage
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.11,0:30:13.17,English1,,0,0,0,,along with countless other species
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.21,0:30:17.41,English1,,0,0,0,,in an unparalleled environmental disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.96,0:30:29.56,English1,,0,0,0,,The apocalypse began in what is now Siberia,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.59,0:30:34.23,English1,,0,0,0,,with volcanic eruptions on a scale unlike anything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:36.43,English1,,0,0,0,,in human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.88,0:30:51.41,English1,,0,0,0,,Earth was very different then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.45,0:30:55.75,English1,,0,0,0,,with one single supercontinent and one great ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.78,0:30:58.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Relentless floods of fiery lava
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.29,0:31:01.06,English1,,0,0,0,,engulfed an area larger than Western Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.09,0:31:03.76,English1,,0,0,0,,The pulsing eruptions went on for\Nhundreds of thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.79,0:31:05.93,English1,,0,0,0,,The pulsing eruptions went on for\Nhundreds of thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.96,0:31:07.53,English1,,0,0,0,,The molten rock
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.56,0:31:10.27,English1,,0,0,0,,ignited coal deposits and polluted the air
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.30,0:31:13.27,English1,,0,0,0,,with carbon dioxide and other greenhouse gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.30,0:31:15.20,English1,,0,0,0,,This heated the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.24,0:31:18.34,English1,,0,0,0,,and stopped the ocean currents from circulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.36,0:31:35.66,English1,,0,0,0,,Noxious bacteria bloomed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.69,0:31:39.83,English1,,0,0,0,,but nearly everything else in the seas died.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.86,0:31:43.43,English1,,0,0,0,,The stagnant waters belched\Ndeadly hydrogen sulfide gas into the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.47,0:31:44.90,English1,,0,0,0,,The stagnant waters belched\Ndeadly hydrogen sulfide gas into the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.93,0:31:47.47,English1,,0,0,0,,which suffocated most of the land animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.48,0:32:04.82,English1,,0,0,0,,Nine in ten of all species on the planet went extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.85,0:32:06.92,English1,,0,0,0,,We call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.96,0:32:08.96,English1,,0,0,0,,The Great Dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.57,0:32:24.21,English1,,0,0,0,,Life on Earth came so near to being wiped out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.24,0:32:28.04,English1,,0,0,0,,that it took more than ten million years to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.08,0:32:30.38,English1,,0,0,0,,But new life-forms slowly evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.41,0:32:34.08,English1,,0,0,0,,to fill the openings left by the Permian holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.86,0:32:44.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Among the biggest winners were the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.76,0:32:47.56,English1,,0,0,0,,Now the Earth was their planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:51.83,English1,,0,0,0,,Their reign continued for over 150 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.87,0:32:54.47,English1,,0,0,0,,Until it, too, came crashing down
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.50,0:32:57.41,English1,,0,0,0,,in another mass extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.44,0:33:00.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Life on Earth has taken quite a beating over the eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.08,0:33:02.88,English1,,0,0,0,,And yet it's still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.91,0:33:05.71,English1,,0,0,0,,The tenacity of life is mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.75,0:33:08.55,English1,,0,0,0,,We keep finding it where no one thought it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.02,0:33:16.32,English1,,0,0,0,,That nameless corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.36,0:33:18.36,English1,,0,0,0,,That's for another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.87,0:33:27.44,English1,,0,0,0,,I know an animal that can live in boiling water
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.47,0:33:29.60,English1,,0,0,0,,or in solid ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.64,0:33:32.01,English1,,0,0,0,,It can go ten years without a drop of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.04,0:33:34.68,English1,,0,0,0,,It can travel naked in the cold vacuum
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.71,0:33:39.21,English1,,0,0,0,,and intense radiation of space and will return unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.25,0:33:41.68,English1,,0,0,0,,The tardigrade, or water bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.72,0:33:44.79,English1,,0,0,0,,It's equally at home atop the tallest mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.82,0:33:46.62,English1,,0,0,0,,and in the deepest trenches of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.66,0:33:49.69,English1,,0,0,0,,And in our own backyards, where they live among the moss
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.73,0:33:52.19,English1,,0,0,0,,in countless numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.23,0:33:53.60,English1,,0,0,0,,You've probably never noticed them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.63,0:33:55.10,English1,,0,0,0,,because they're so small.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.13,0:33:56.73,English1,,0,0,0,,About the size of a pinpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.77,0:33:58.47,English1,,0,0,0,,But they're tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.50,0:34:02.77,English1,,0,0,0,,The tardigrades have survived all five mass extinctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.81,0:34:05.54,English1,,0,0,0,,They've been in business for a half a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.57,0:34:07.91,English1,,0,0,0,,We used to think that life was finicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.94,0:34:09.88,English1,,0,0,0,,that it would only take hold where it was
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.91,0:34:11.88,English1,,0,0,0,,not too hot, not too cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.91,0:34:15.65,English1,,0,0,0,,not too dark or salty or acidic or radioactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.68,0:34:18.45,English1,,0,0,0,,And whatever you do, don't forget to add water.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.49,0:34:20.22,English1,,0,0,0,,We were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.26,0:34:21.56,English1,,0,0,0,,As the hardy tardigrade demonstrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.59,0:34:23.76,English1,,0,0,0,,life can endure conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.79,0:34:27.00,English1,,0,0,0,,that would mean certain death for us humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.03,0:34:28.83,English1,,0,0,0,,But differences between us and life found
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.86,0:34:31.40,English1,,0,0,0,,in even the most extreme environments on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.43,0:34:34.40,English1,,0,0,0,,are only variations on a single theme,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.44,0:34:36.97,English1,,0,0,0,,dialects of a single language.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.01,0:34:39.77,English1,,0,0,0,,The genetic code of Earth life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.71,0:34:47.25,English1,,0,0,0,,But what would life be like on other worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:50.29,English1,,0,0,0,,Worlds with a completely different history,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.32,0:34:53.32,English1,,0,0,0,,chemistry and evolution from our planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.79,0:34:59.33,English1,,0,0,0,,There's a distant world I want to take you to--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.36,0:35:01.76,English1,,0,0,0,,a world far different from our own,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.80,0:35:05.13,English1,,0,0,0,,but one that may harbor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.17,0:35:09.04,English1,,0,0,0,,If it does, it promises to be unlike anything
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.07,0:35:11.51,English1,,0,0,0,,we've ever seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.12,0:35:30.49,English1,,0,0,0,,Clouds and haze completely hide the surface of Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.52,0:35:32.49,English1,,0,0,0,,Saturn's giant moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.52,0:35:35.09,English1,,0,0,0,,Titan reminds me a little bit of home.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.13,0:35:38.60,English1,,0,0,0,,Like Earth, it has an atmosphere that's mostly nitrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.63,0:35:40.76,English1,,0,0,0,,But it's four times denser.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:43.67,English1,,0,0,0,,Titan's air has no oxygen at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.70,0:35:46.17,English1,,0,0,0,,And it's far colder than anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.20,0:35:49.81,English1,,0,0,0,,But still... I want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.98,0:35:53.48,English1,,0,0,0,,We have to descend
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.51,0:35:55.95,English1,,0,0,0,,through a couple hundred kilometers of smog
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.98,0:35:58.95,English1,,0,0,0,,before we can even see the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.98,0:36:02.52,English1,,0,0,0,,But hidden beneath lies a weirdly familiar landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.23,0:36:13.66,English1,,0,0,0,,Titan is the only other world in the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.70,0:36:15.13,English1,,0,0,0,,where it ever rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.17,0:36:18.57,English1,,0,0,0,,It has rivers and coastlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.51,0:36:25.58,English1,,0,0,0,,Titan has hundreds of lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.61,0:36:29.15,English1,,0,0,0,,One of them larger than Lake Superior in North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.18,0:36:31.15,English1,,0,0,0,,Vapor rising from the lakes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.18,0:36:33.38,English1,,0,0,0,,condenses and falls again as rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.42,0:36:37.32,English1,,0,0,0,,The rain feeds rivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.36,0:36:40.66,English1,,0,0,0,,which carve valleys into the landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.69,0:36:42.69,English1,,0,0,0,,just like on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.96,0:36:47.03,English1,,0,0,0,,But with one big difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.07,0:36:49.77,English1,,0,0,0,,On Titan, the seas and the rain
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.80,0:36:53.70,English1,,0,0,0,,are made not of water but of methane and ethane.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.74,0:36:56.67,English1,,0,0,0,,On Earth, those molecules form natural gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.71,0:36:59.54,English1,,0,0,0,,On frigid Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.58,0:37:01.58,English1,,0,0,0,,they're liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.89,0:37:08.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Titan has lots of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.92,0:37:11.62,English1,,0,0,0,,but all of it is frozen hard as rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.66,0:37:14.02,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, the landscape and mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.06,0:37:16.53,English1,,0,0,0,,are made mainly of water ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.56,0:37:18.76,English1,,0,0,0,,At hundreds of degrees below zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.80,0:37:22.70,English1,,0,0,0,,Titan is far too cold for water to ever be liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.94,0:37:28.14,English1,,0,0,0,,Astrobiologists since Carl Sagan have wondered
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.17,0:37:31.61,English1,,0,0,0,,if life might swim in Titan's hydrocarbon lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.95,0:37:35.88,English1,,0,0,0,,The chemical basis for such life
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.91,0:37:39.32,English1,,0,0,0,,would have to be entirely\Ndifferent from anything we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.35,0:37:42.15,English1,,0,0,0,,All life on Earth depends on liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.19,0:37:44.49,English1,,0,0,0,,And Titan's surface has none of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.52,0:37:47.06,English1,,0,0,0,,But we can imagine other kinds of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.09,0:37:49.66,English1,,0,0,0,,There might be creatures that inhale hydrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.69,0:37:51.16,English1,,0,0,0,,instead of oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.20,0:37:54.67,English1,,0,0,0,,And exhale methane instead of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.70,0:37:58.14,English1,,0,0,0,,They might use acetylene instead\Nof sugar as an energy source.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.17,0:38:00.60,English1,,0,0,0,,How could we find out if such creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.64,0:38:05.14,English1,,0,0,0,,rule a hidden empire beneath the oil-dark waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.39,0:38:23.66,English1,,0,0,0,,We're diving down deep into the Kraken Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.70,0:38:26.70,English1,,0,0,0,,named for the mythic Norse sea monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.07,0:38:32.27,English1,,0,0,0,,Even if there is {\i1}one of those down there,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.30,0:38:33.97,English1,,0,0,0,,we probably couldn't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.01,0:38:36.54,English1,,0,0,0,,It's so dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.58,0:38:40.98,English1,,0,0,0,,If you took all the oil and natural gas on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.01,0:38:44.75,English1,,0,0,0,,it would amount to but a tiny fraction of Titan's reserves.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.25,0:38:50.19,English1,,0,0,0,,Let's turn on some lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.49,0:38:57.93,English1,,0,0,0,,We're now 200 meters beneath the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.20,0:39:03.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Did you see something?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.77,0:39:06.97,English1,,0,0,0,,Over there, by that vent.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.01,0:39:09.47,English1,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was just my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.51,0:39:11.48,English1,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll have to come back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.51,0:39:14.51,English1,,0,0,0,,if we want to find out for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.75,0:39:20.38,English1,,0,0,0,,There's one last story I want to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.42,0:39:24.59,English1,,0,0,0,,And it's the greatest story science has ever told.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.93,0:39:32.36,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the story of life on our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.82,0:39:57.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the Earth of four billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.96,0:40:01.63,English1,,0,0,0,,This was our planet before life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.66,0:40:04.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows how life got started.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.76,0:40:07.13,English1,,0,0,0,,Most of the evidence\Nfrom that time was destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.17,0:40:09.77,English1,,0,0,0,,by impact and erosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.80,0:40:13.57,English1,,0,0,0,,Science works on the frontier\Nbetween knowledge and ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.61,0:40:15.54,English1,,0,0,0,,We're not afraid to admit what we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.57,0:40:17.88,English1,,0,0,0,,There's no shame in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.91,0:40:21.75,English1,,0,0,0,,The only shame is to pretend\Nthat we have all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.78,0:40:23.45,English1,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone watching this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.48,0:40:25.98,English1,,0,0,0,,will be the first to solve the mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.02,0:40:28.42,English1,,0,0,0,,of how life on Earth began.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.99,0:40:37.83,English1,,0,0,0,,The evidence from living microbes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.86,0:40:39.76,English1,,0,0,0,,suggest that their earliest ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.80,0:40:41.50,English1,,0,0,0,,preferred high temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.53,0:40:44.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Life on Earth may have arisen in hot water
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.47,0:40:46.77,English1,,0,0,0,,around submerged volcanic vents.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.54,0:40:54.01,English1,,0,0,0,,In Carl Sagan's original Cosmos{\i1} series,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.05,0:40:56.81,English1,,0,0,0,,he traced the unbroken thread that stretches
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.85,0:40:58.92,English1,,0,0,0,,directly from the one-celled organisms
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.95,0:41:01.49,English1,,0,0,0,,of nearly four billion years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.52,0:41:03.79,English1,,0,0,0,,to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.82,0:41:06.96,English1,,0,0,0,,Four billion years in 40 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.99,0:41:10.53,English1,,0,0,0,,From creatures who had yet to discern day from night
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.56,0:41:14.37,English1,,0,0,0,,to beings who are exploring the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.52,0:42:06.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Those are some of the things that molecules do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.55,0:42:10.02,English1,,0,0,0,,given four billion years of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.51,0:42:20.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Sync and corrections by n17t01\Nwww.addic7ed.com
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.80,0:00:05.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是关于你的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.37,0:00:08.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也关于我和你的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:17.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不久之前  在狗出现之前
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.51,0:00:19.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们以前不存在
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.18,0:00:22.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在的狗有大有小 宠物狗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.65,0:00:24.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,守护犬  猎犬
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.22,0:00:26.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,各式各样的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.82,0:00:29.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,怎么会这样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.39,0:00:30.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是狗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.69,0:00:31.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形形色色的各种生物
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.93,0:00:34.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是从哪里来的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.70,0:00:39.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,答案是来自能量的转换  听上去可能
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.07,0:00:41.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,像是童话或者神话
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.70,0:00:43.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但并非如此
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.93,0:02:20.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们回到3万年前 狗狗诞生前
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.84,0:02:23.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时我们的祖先生活在最后一次冰河时代的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.01,0:02:25.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无尽冬夜
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.01,0:02:29.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的祖先小规模的群居 游荡着
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.54,0:02:31.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们睡在星空下
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.85,0:02:35.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星星就是他们的故事书  日历
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.15,0:02:38.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生活指南
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.15,0:02:40.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星星告诉他们严寒何时到来
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.86,0:02:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谷物何时成熟
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.86,0:02:46.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,鹿群和野牛群何时迁徙
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.46,0:02:50.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们对家的印象就是地球本身
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.46,0:02:54.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是他们受到其他饥饿生物的威胁
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.20,0:02:56.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如狮子和熊
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.34,0:02:58.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与他们抢夺同样地猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:03:01.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有狼群会掠食他们中
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.74,0:03:03.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最脆弱的同伴
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.10,0:03:24.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有的狼都想来分一杯羹
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:26.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但大部分都不敢靠的太近
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.67,0:03:29.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们的恐惧来自血液中
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.17,0:03:30.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,高浓度的应激激素
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.01,0:03:32.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是生死攸关的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:35.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为靠的太近可能很致命
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:38.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但也有些狼  因为自然差异
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.91,0:03:40.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种激素浓度较低
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.72,0:03:43.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使得它们不是那么惧怕人类
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.06,0:03:49.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这头狼和他祖先
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:51.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中的一个分支发现了同样的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.19,0:03:53.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约在1万5千年前
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.19,0:03:56.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个完美的生存策略
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.20,0:03:59.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类的驯化
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.47,0:04:03.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在人类捕猎时别威胁到他们
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.04,0:04:05.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们会允许你以残渣为食
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.04,0:04:08.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你吃的更规律 就可以繁衍更多的后代
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.24,0:04:11.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些后代会继承你的性情
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.08,0:04:14.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种驯养的淘汰方式
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,效果逐代加强
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.62,0:04:21.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到这一系的野狼进化为
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.46,0:04:23.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,狗
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.56,0:04:26.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以称它为最友善的生存
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在看来 这也是对人类非常有利的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.24,0:04:37.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些吃剩饭的狗并不只是收拾垃圾
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.57,0:04:39.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们也是保安力量
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.79,0:04:58.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着这种不同物种间的合作
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:01.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,狗的外貌也发生了改变
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.86,0:05:04.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可爱变成了优胜劣汰时的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.13,0:05:06.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你越可爱 就有更大的机会活下去
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.67,0:05:10.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并把你的基因传递给下一代
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.10,0:05:12.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,起先是为了便利而结成的联盟
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:16.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成了越来越深厚的友谊
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:17.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接下来发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.01,0:05:20.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们略过2万年前的先祖
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.48,0:05:24.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看看不是很久以前的古人
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.79,0:05:27.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在冰河时代的间歇期
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:31.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}平和的气候带来了一场变革
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.46,0:05:35.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人类不再流浪  而是定居下来
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.13,0:05:39.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}新的事物出现了  村庄
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.07,0:05:40.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人们依然在打猎和采集食物
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.80,0:05:44.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但也开始了制造食物和衣服
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.47,0:05:45.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}农业
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.68,0:05:53.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}狼用他们的自由
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:56.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}来交换稳定的食物供应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.42,0:05:59.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们放弃了选择伙伴的权利
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.19,0:06:02.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人类替他们选择
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.22,0:06:06.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们消灭无法被驯服的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.33,0:06:07.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那些会咬人的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.03,0:06:12.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们繁育那些讨喜的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:18.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}让这些狗服从命令
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.41,0:06:21.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}打猎  放牧  守卫  拖拽重物
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.61,0:06:22.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}陪伴人类
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.71,0:06:24.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从每一窝小狗中
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:27.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}选择那些他们最喜欢的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.35,0:06:29.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一代接一代 狗进化了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:34.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}称之为 人工选择
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:35.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或者  饲养
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.79,0:06:38.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把狼变成狗 是人类第一次
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.06,0:06:41.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亲手干预进化过程
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从那以后我们改进了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:47.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对我们有用的植物和动物
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.47,0:06:51.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}弹指一挥间 大约1万5千到2万年里
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:55.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们把灰狼改变成为了各种各样的可爱的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.08,0:06:56.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们把灰狼改变成为了各种各样的可爱的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.44,0:06:57.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想想看
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:06:59.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}各个品种的狗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:02.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都是人类塑造出来的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.78,0:07:06.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其中大部分 最受欢迎的品种
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.29,0:07:08.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都是最近几百年培育出来的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.79,0:07:13.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进化的强大力量
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:15.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将穷凶极恶的狼
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:18.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}变成忠心耿耿的牧羊犬
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.13,0:07:21.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}保护 看守羊群 并驱赶狼群
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.82,0:07:39.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人工培育 把狼变成狗
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.15,0:07:42.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把野草变成小麦和玉米
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.09,0:07:45.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上 大部分我们食用的植物和动物
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:49.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是来自野生的 不可食用的品种
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:52.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果强大的人工选择可以在1万到1万5千年间
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.97,0:07:55.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带来如此巨大的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么大自然的选择淘汰
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:00.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在上百万年间可以做到怎样的程度呢
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:05.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形形色色美好的生命就是答案
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:07.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,怎么做到得
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:12.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的想象之舟可以带我们去任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:16.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}任何时间 甚至看不见的小宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.66,0:08:20.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在那里 生命可以完成蜕变
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.70,0:08:22.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}跟我来
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:31.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看上去可能不像
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:33.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们曾经生活在冰河时期
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.29,0:08:35.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长达2百万年之久
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.06,0:08:37.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在只是其中一个间歇期
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.63,0:08:39.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,2百万年间的大部分时期
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.43,0:08:41.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,气候又冷又干
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.94,0:08:44.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,北极冰盖比今天所看到的范围更大
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:46.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,北极冰盖比今天所看到的范围更大
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.84,0:08:50.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这漫长的冰川期
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:53.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从北极来的冬季海水冰
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:55.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一直延伸至今日洛杉矶所在的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.65,0:09:00.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大灰熊在冰冻荒芜的爱尔兰游荡
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.96,0:09:08.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这头熊看上去很普通
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:12.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是她的内在却有着不平凡的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:15.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一股催生新物种的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:17.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要探究这股力量
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.27,0:09:20.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们要把比例尺调整到
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,细胞级别
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.61,0:09:26.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这样才能探究熊的生殖系统
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.35,0:09:34.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们通过锁骨下的动脉穿过心脏
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}快到了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:06.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是一些她的卵子
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.92,0:10:09.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要想了解这些卵子的详情
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:11.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们必须变得更小
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.39,0:10:14.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,缩小到分子级别
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.36,0:10:20.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的想象之舟有多小呢
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:24.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有一颗沙粒的百万分之一
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.37,0:10:28.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到那些阔步前进的小家伙吗
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.34,0:10:31.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们是蛋白质 叫做驱动蛋白
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:34.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些驱动蛋白是搬运工
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.35,0:10:37.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,忙碌地在细胞间传递货物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.18,0:10:39.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长得就像外星人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.05,0:10:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们和其他长相类似的小家伙
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.86,0:10:47.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,存在于每个活细胞中 包括我们的细胞
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:52.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果生命体也有圣殿
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.23,0:10:56.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就是细胞核 包含了我们的DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.10,0:10:59.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们遗传密码的远古圣经
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.81,0:11:04.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由所有生命体都能理解的语言写成
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.39,0:11:15.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}DNA是一种长螺旋阶梯状的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:17.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也叫双螺旋结构
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.29,0:11:19.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,阶梯的横档是由4种
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.09,0:11:21.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不同的小分子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:24.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些就是基因字母表中的字母
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:27.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些字母的特定排列组合
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生出针对所有生命体的指令
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.84,0:11:33.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,告诉它们如果生长 移动 消化
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:36.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,感知环境 愈合 繁殖
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:39.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,DNA双螺旋就是一台分子机器
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.95,0:11:43.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由1千亿称之为原子的部件组成
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:47.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,单个DNA分子中的原子数量
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.62,0:11:51.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多的就像银河系中的繁星数量
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.43,0:11:53.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和狗一样
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.53,0:11:56.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和熊一样
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.13,0:11:59.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和所有生物一样
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:03.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们 每一个人 就是一个小宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.38,0:12:15.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}DNA信息在细胞与细胞间
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:17.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也在一代接一代的繁衍中异常谨慎地复制着
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.45,0:12:19.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也在一代接一代的繁衍中异常谨慎地复制着
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.19,0:12:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当一条松开的蛋白质分开双螺旋的两条边
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:26.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,拆开中间的横档
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.29,0:12:28.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,新的DNA分子就诞生了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.20,0:12:30.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,细胞核的液体中
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.53,0:12:34.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,遗传密码的分子字母自由的游动
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:37.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,双螺旋的其中一边复制着失去的另外一边
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.87,0:12:40.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成两个完全一样的DNA分子
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:43.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是生命体繁衍和传递基因的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.91,0:12:45.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}代代相传
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.98,0:12:48.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当一个活细胞分裂成两个
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:53.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每个细胞都带有一份完整的DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.09,0:12:56.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一种特定的蛋白质负责校对
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.86,0:12:58.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}确保只接受正确的字母
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.69,0:13:01.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这保证了DNA的准确复制
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.56,0:13:03.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是没有什么是完美的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.33,0:13:06.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}偶尔 校对也会发生失误
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.53,0:13:10.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在遗传指令中产生了细微的随机变化
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.34,0:13:13.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这头熊的卵子细胞中发生了突变
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.57,0:13:17.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如此细微的随机事件也会带来
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:19.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}很大的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:26.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}突变改变了控制毛皮颜色的基因
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:29.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它影响了这只熊的后代的深色毛皮的产生
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.62,0:13:31.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它影响了这只熊的后代的深色毛皮的产生
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:33.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大多数突变是无害的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:35.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有些是致命的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.70,0:13:38.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}少数 纯属偶然 使得某个生物
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.60,0:13:42.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在竞争中获得重大优势
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:44.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}1年后
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.31,0:13:46.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这只熊做了母亲
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.14,0:13:47.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}作为突变的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:51.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其中一只熊宝宝生来就是白色的皮毛
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:54.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当两只熊长大到可以自己猎食时
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.28,0:13:56.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}哪头熊更可能
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:14:00.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}悄悄地接近它们的猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:04.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}棕熊和雪区别明显  很远就能被察觉
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.06,0:14:06.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}白熊子孙满堂 并把它独特的基因
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:08.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}传递下去
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:11.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这样的情况不断发生
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:13.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}再接下去的几代里
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.97,0:14:16.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}白色皮毛的基因散播遍及整个北极的熊
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.57,0:14:19.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}白色皮毛的基因散播遍及整个北极的熊
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:21.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}深色皮毛的基因消亡在
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.98,0:14:24.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生存的竞争中
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.75,0:14:30.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,突变是完全随机并且时刻发生的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:32.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是环境会奖励那些
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:34.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对生存有利的突变
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.92,0:14:37.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大自然选择那些可以更好适应环境的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.32,0:14:39.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大自然选择那些可以更好适应环境的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.99,0:14:42.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种选择绝对不是随机的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:48.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}两个种群的熊各自分开
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.14,0:14:49.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}经过了上千年
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:53.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进化出各自独有的特征
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.17,0:14:56.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们变成了不同的物种
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:00.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是查尔斯 达尔文
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.88,0:15:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在《物种起源》中发表的思想
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.55,0:15:07.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}单个的熊不会进化
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:11.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一群熊在几代繁衍中进化
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:14.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果北极的冰日益减少
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:18.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全球变暖的缘故 北极熊可能灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.53,0:15:20.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们会被棕熊取代
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.57,0:15:23.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以更好地适应冰融后的环境
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:28.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个故事和狗的进化不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:30.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有人去指导这个变化
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:34.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们都是由自然环境选择的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.25,0:15:36.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是自然选择
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:40.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学历史上最颠覆性的理论
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:44.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1859年 达尔文首次提出了支持这个理论的证据
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.89,0:15:48.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它带来的争议从未消退
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.93,0:15:50.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.23,0:16:00.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们都可以理解那种令人不适的刺痛
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.36,0:16:03.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们竟然是猩猩变的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.63,0:16:06.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亲戚最能让我们感到丢脸
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:09.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的近亲  黑猩猩
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.20,0:16:11.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们频繁在公共场合做出不当的举止
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:14.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人类想和它们保持距离也是可以理解的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:16.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人类想和它们保持距离也是可以理解的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:18.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,传统信仰的核心前提
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.65,0:16:20.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们是造物者特制的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.65,0:16:22.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和其他动物有区别的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.65,0:16:25.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种观点也很容易被理解
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:28.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它让我们觉得 与众不同
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.26,0:16:32.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们和这些树是亲戚呢
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:34.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你又作何感想
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.44,0:16:45.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是橡树DNA的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.71,0:16:47.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把它看做条形码
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.88,0:16:50.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命代码的指令
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:53.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}告诉这个树如何分解糖分
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.51,0:16:56.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}拿它和我自己的DNA作比较
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.02,0:17:03.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}DNA不会撒谎
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.96,0:17:07.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这棵树就是我失散已久的表亲
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:09.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不单单是树
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.30,0:17:12.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果回到很久以前 我们可以发现
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.20,0:17:14.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们有着共同的祖先
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:15.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,蝴蝶
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.57,0:17:17.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,灰狼
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:18.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,蘑菇
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.61,0:17:20.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,鲨鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:21.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,细菌
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.71,0:17:23.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,麻雀
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.04,0:17:24.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,幸福的一家人
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.61,0:17:28.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,条形码的其他部分因人而异
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:31.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也使得猫头鹰和章鱼有所区别
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.39,0:17:33.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,除非你有一个同卵双胞胎
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:35.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个世界上不会有人
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.92,0:17:38.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和你有着相同的DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.59,0:17:40.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他的物种中 遗传基因的不同
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:44.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为自然选择提供了原材料
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.23,0:17:48.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,环境决定了什么基因可以生存繁衍
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.17,0:17:50.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说到生物遗传基因的指令中
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:52.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最基本的功能
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.34,0:17:55.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比方说分解糖分  我们和其他物种
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.14,0:17:57.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几乎一致
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:18:00.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为这些是生命最基本的功能
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:03.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们在各种不同生命形式诞生前
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.25,0:18:05.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就已经进化完成
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.25,0:18:07.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是我们的生命之树
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:09.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}科学使我们可以
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.26,0:18:11.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为地球上的所有生物
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.43,0:18:13.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}绘制这份家谱
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.43,0:18:17.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}相近基因的亲戚住在同一根的枝干上
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.26,0:18:20.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}差异越大住的越远
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:23.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每支细枝都是一个物种
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.07,0:18:28.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}主杆代表着地球上所有生命的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.28,0:18:31.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}共同祖先
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:33.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命具有很高的可塑性
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.51,0:18:36.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命一旦出现  环境就开始
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:39.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将它塑造出惊人数量的不同形态
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.79,0:18:43.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}比我们所能展示的还多1万倍
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.59,0:18:47.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生物学家已经编录了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:51.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}50万种不同的甲壳虫
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.97,0:18:56.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更别提那些数之不尽的细菌
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:18:58.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更别提那些数之不尽的细菌
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.27,0:19:00.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有几百万种不同种类的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:03.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}动物和植物  其中大部分
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:05.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}依然未知
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.45,0:19:08.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这么说吧  我们至今还没有见过
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.55,0:19:11.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大部分的陆栖生物
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:14.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们这个小小星球上就是有这么多种的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:16.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们这个小小星球上就是有这么多种的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.06,0:19:20.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命之树将触角伸向所有的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.63,0:19:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}探寻可行的办法
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.23,0:19:23.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为新的生命形式
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.96,0:19:26.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}创造新的环境和机会
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.37,0:19:33.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命之树已经35亿岁了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.14,0:19:35.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}时间已经长的可以发展出
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:38.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有令人惊奇的本领
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.92,0:19:43.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进化可以使一种动物
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.58,0:19:46.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}伪装成植物
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.52,0:19:52.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}花费了数千代的努力
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:55.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}去设计一套精心制作的服饰
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.70,0:19:57.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}用来欺骗捕食者的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:20:00.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}用来欺骗捕食者的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:04.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或者植物伪装成动物的模样
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.10,0:20:07.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}花朵进化出黄蜂般的外表
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:11.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}兰花就用这种方式诱使黄蜂为他授粉
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.28,0:20:14.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是强大的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:17.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自然选择下的变形本领
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:29.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在密集杂乱的巨大生命之树上
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.23,0:20:31.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.40,0:20:35.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}数不胜数的众多分支中的一小支
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.70,0:20:40.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}科学揭示了所有生命本是同源
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.38,0:20:46.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,达尔文发现了真正的进化机制
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.58,0:20:49.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,过去普遍的观点是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:52.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,种类繁多的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.29,0:20:55.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,必然是有造物主创造的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.26,0:20:58.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分别创造了几百万种不同的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.43,0:21:01.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种观点认为 生物实在是太复杂了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:05.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不可能由未经引导的进化而来
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:07.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像人的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.97,0:21:10.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个极其复杂的杰作
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.87,0:21:15.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要有角膜
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.01,0:21:19.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}虹膜 晶状体 视网膜
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.48,0:21:21.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}视神经 肌肉群
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:24.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}再配合大脑复制的神经网络
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.62,0:21:27.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}才能产生一幅图像
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.56,0:21:30.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它远比其他任何一个人类制造的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.46,0:21:33.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}物体要来的复杂
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:35.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所以 结论是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.23,0:21:37.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人眼不可能是无意识的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.30,0:21:39.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进化产物
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:43.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要了解真相 我们需要回到
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.67,0:21:47.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们有能力看之前
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.82,0:22:06.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最初
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.42,0:22:08.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命都是瞎子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.09,0:22:12.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是我们的世界 40亿年前的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.26,0:22:14.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是我们的世界 40亿年前的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.26,0:22:17.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那时还没有眼睛可以视物
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.93,0:22:20.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}直到几亿年过去
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.00,0:22:22.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}突然有一天
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.63,0:22:24.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个细菌的DNA产生了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.70,0:22:26.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}细微的复制错误
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.27,0:22:28.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个随机的突变给了这个微生物
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.01,0:22:31.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个可以吸收阳光的蛋白质分子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.81,0:22:33.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想知道感光细菌的世界是什么样子的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.65,0:22:35.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想知道感光细菌的世界是什么样子的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.35,0:22:38.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看看屏幕的右边
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.65,0:22:42.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}突变继续随机的发生
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.29,0:22:45.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在其他所有的生物身上
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.53,0:22:49.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}另一个突变
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:53.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}使得细菌可以逃离强烈的阳光
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.63,0:22:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}发生了什么事
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.03,0:22:57.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}黑夜和白昼
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.80,0:22:59.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些可以区分亮光的细菌
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.84,0:23:02.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}相对其他细菌有了一个决定性的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.51,0:23:04.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.34,0:23:07.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为日光带着强烈的紫外线
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.51,0:23:09.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}会损伤DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.48,0:23:13.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}敏感的细菌避开强烈的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:15.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在暗处安全的交换DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.59,0:23:17.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们比其他生活在表面的细菌
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.52,0:23:19.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更多的存活下来
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.99,0:23:23.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}日积月累 这些光敏蛋白质
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.10,0:23:25.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在更高级的单细胞生物身上
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.73,0:23:29.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}浓缩成一个色素点
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.03,0:23:32.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这使寻找光亮成为可能
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.24,0:23:34.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对于需要阳光合成食物的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.37,0:23:37.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命体来说 这是个压倒性的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.78,0:23:47.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是扁平虫眼中的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.72,0:23:49.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个多细胞生物
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.89,0:23:52.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在色素点中进化出一个小坑
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.22,0:23:54.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}碗状的凹痕
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.53,0:23:57.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}使动物可以区别明暗
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.90,0:24:01.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大致看出周围的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.27,0:24:05.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}包括食物和天敌
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.30,0:24:07.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}非常了不起的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.87,0:24:10.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}随后 影像更清晰了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.54,0:24:12.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}小坑变深了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.28,0:24:15.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进化成一个有开口的凹槽
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.05,0:24:17.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}经过几千代
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.42,0:24:20.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自然选择逐渐塑造出眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.42,0:24:25.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}开放的地方凝聚成一个小孔
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.59,0:24:27.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}由一层保护性的透明薄膜覆盖
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.93,0:24:30.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只允许一点点的光线透过小孔
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.43,0:24:32.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但也足够在敏感的眼睛内部表面
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.83,0:24:35.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}描绘出一幅模糊的图像
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.40,0:24:37.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这演变出了聚焦
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.30,0:24:39.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更大的孔可以让更多的光线通过
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.64,0:24:43.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}产生更亮的图像  但却失去了焦点
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.24,0:24:46.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个新形态引发了视觉的军备竞赛
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.15,0:24:48.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个新形态引发了视觉的军备竞赛
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.19,0:25:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}竞争者们需要跟上才能生存
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.80,0:25:07.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个新的绝妙特征出现了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.53,0:25:12.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可以同时保证亮度和清晰焦点的晶状体
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.54,0:25:14.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在远古的鱼类眼中
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.97,0:25:18.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}小孔附近的透明胶体形成了晶状体
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.71,0:25:21.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}同时 小孔扩大了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.48,0:25:23.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}允许更多的光线通过
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.55,0:25:25.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}鱼的视界高清了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.98,0:25:29.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不论远近
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.72,0:25:33.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然而 可怕的事情发生了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.36,0:25:36.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你注意到一杯水中的吸管
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.86,0:25:39.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看上去在水面处是弯的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.36,0:25:42.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那是因为光线从一个介质进入另一个介质时发生了折射
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.13,0:25:45.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像从水到空气
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.04,0:25:48.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的眼睛最初是为了在水中视物
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.81,0:25:51.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}眼中的水状液体巧妙地
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.71,0:25:55.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}消除了折射的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.48,0:25:58.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是对于陆地动物
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.68,0:26:01.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在空气中成像的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.09,0:26:04.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进入它们湿润的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.19,0:26:05.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光线发生折射
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.76,0:26:09.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}造成全面的失真
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.76,0:26:12.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们的两栖祖先从水中登陆时
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.53,0:26:15.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原本在水中精确视物的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.77,0:26:18.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,却在空气中一塌糊涂
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.10,0:26:20.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从那时起我们的视力一直不好
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.77,0:26:23.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们一直认为我们的眼睛是最高级的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.71,0:26:26.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但直到3.75亿年后
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.61,0:26:29.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们依然无法看清近在眼前的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.05,0:26:31.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者像鱼那样在昏暗环境中辨别细节
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.72,0:26:33.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者像鱼那样在昏暗环境中辨别细节
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.62,0:26:35.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们离开水里时
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.12,0:26:37.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么大自然不能从新来过
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.29,0:26:38.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进化出一对新的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.92,0:26:41.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以在空气中清晰视物
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.26,0:26:43.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大自然并不是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.36,0:26:46.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进化过程对于已有的结构的改变
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.77,0:26:48.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是世世代代的慢慢适应
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.97,0:26:50.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不可能一切推倒重来
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.64,0:26:52.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不可能一切推倒重来
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.47,0:26:56.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进化中眼睛 在每一步的发展中
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.04,0:26:57.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都为我们的生存提供了极大的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.78,0:27:00.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都为我们的生存提供了极大的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.95,0:27:03.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在现在存活的动物身上 我们发现了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.82,0:27:06.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}各个发展阶段的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.26,0:27:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们都很实用
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.59,0:27:15.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人类眼睛的复杂程度对进化过程来说
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.76,0:27:17.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有丝毫难度
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.90,0:27:22.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}事实上 没有进化就根本无法解释眼睛和其他生物学
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.40,0:27:24.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}事实上 没有进化就根本无法解释眼睛和其他生物学
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.07,0:27:26.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有人说进化论只是一种理论
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.74,0:27:29.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只不过是一种观点
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.94,0:27:32.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进化论就和万有引力定律一样
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.68,0:27:34.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是科学的事实
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.78,0:27:37.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进化确有其事
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.52,0:27:39.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,承认我们和其他生物出自同源
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.95,0:27:41.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并不只是严谨的科学
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.02,0:27:47.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我看来 这也是一种崇高的心灵体验
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.97,0:27:56.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为进化是盲目地
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.84,0:28:01.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它无法预测或改变悲剧的发生
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.11,0:28:04.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命之树有一些断裂的分支
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.94,0:28:08.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其中大部分发生在5次最大的灾难中
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:09.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其中大部分发生在5次最大的灾难中
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.32,0:28:12.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}某个地方 有着一座纪念堂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.32,0:28:15.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}纪念着消失的物种
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.32,0:28:17.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}灭绝物种的纪念堂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.49,0:28:19.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}随我来
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.29,0:28:31.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,_
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.63,0:28:34.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到灭绝物种的纪念堂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.65,0:28:39.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,纪念着生命之树上的断枝
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.46,0:28:53.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于依然存在的上百万种生物来说
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.20,0:28:57.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能上千种正在垂死挣扎
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.47,0:28:59.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们中大部分在与其他生命形式的日常竞争中绝种
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.97,0:29:01.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们中大部分在与其他生命形式的日常竞争中绝种
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.54,0:29:05.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但也有很多是被地球上无法抗拒的大灾难灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.14,0:29:07.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但也有很多是被地球上无法抗拒的大灾难灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.38,0:29:09.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在过去的5亿年里
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.81,0:29:12.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发生过5次
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.52,0:29:17.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,5次灭绝地球生命的大灾难
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.72,0:29:22.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最惨的一次发生在2.5亿年前
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:25.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个纪元的终结
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.56,0:29:28.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,称之 二叠纪
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.38,0:29:47.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三叶虫像装甲部队一样
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.15,0:29:49.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,成群结队的在海床上肆虐
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.65,0:29:52.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们是第一批进化出可以成像的眼睛的动物
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.35,0:29:54.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们是第一批进化出可以成像的眼睛的动物
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.33,0:30:01.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三叶虫繁荣了大约2.7亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.36,0:30:04.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球曾是三叶虫的天下
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.93,0:30:08.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它们现在都没了 绝种了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.37,0:30:11.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们中最后的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.11,0:30:13.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也随着其他物种一起
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.21,0:30:17.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在空前的环境灾难中绝种了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.96,0:30:29.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大灾难发生在今日西伯利亚的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.59,0:30:34.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一场规模无比巨大的火山喷发
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:36.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一场规模无比巨大的火山喷发
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.88,0:30:51.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时地球很不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.45,0:30:55.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有一个超质大陆板块和一片大洋
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.78,0:30:58.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无情的滚烫的熔浆
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.29,0:31:01.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,洪水般吞没了比西欧还大的区域
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.09,0:31:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,断断续续的喷发持续了几十万年
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.79,0:31:05.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,断断续续的喷发持续了几十万年
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.96,0:31:07.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,融化的岩石
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.56,0:31:10.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,点燃了煤层 并且 污染了大气
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.30,0:31:13.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,充斥着二氧化碳和其他温室气体
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.30,0:31:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球温度升高
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.24,0:31:18.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,洋流停止了流动
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.36,0:31:35.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有害的细菌迅速繁殖
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.69,0:31:39.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海中其他生物几乎全部灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.86,0:31:43.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,腐臭的水散发出致命的硫化氢气体
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.47,0:31:44.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,腐臭的水散发出致命的硫化氢气体
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.93,0:31:47.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,导致大多数陆地生物窒息
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.48,0:32:04.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,百分之九十的物种灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.85,0:32:06.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们称之为
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.96,0:32:08.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.57,0:32:24.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球上的生命差一点全部绝种
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.24,0:32:28.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,需要花费上千万年才能恢复
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.08,0:32:30.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是新的生命形式在慢慢进化
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.41,0:32:34.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开始填补由二叠纪大屠杀遗留的空缺
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.86,0:32:44.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恐龙就是其中的大赢家
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.76,0:32:47.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在地球是它们的天下
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:51.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们的统治持续了1.5亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.87,0:32:54.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是在一次大灾难中
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.50,0:32:57.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不可避免的土崩瓦解
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.44,0:33:00.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球上的生命从太古时期就饱受摧残
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.08,0:33:02.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,却依然存在
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.91,0:33:05.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命顽强得令人惊讶
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.75,0:33:08.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们总是能找到一条意想不到的生存之路
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.02,0:33:16.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到那条无名走廊吗
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.36,0:33:18.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以后再说
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.87,0:33:27.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有种动物可以活在沸腾的水中
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.47,0:33:29.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或者坚固的冰层中
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.64,0:33:32.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可以10年不喝一滴水
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.04,0:33:34.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可以不加防护的穿过寒冷真空
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.71,0:33:39.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并且充满强烈辐射的太空 而毫发无损
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.25,0:33:41.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}节肢动物 又叫  缓步类动物
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.72,0:33:44.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1} 生活在最高的高山还是最深的海沟
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.82,0:33:46.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对它们来说没有区别
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.66,0:33:49.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们生活在苔藓中  就在我们周围
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.73,0:33:52.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}数也数不清
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.23,0:33:53.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可能从没注意到它们
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.63,0:33:55.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它们太小了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.13,0:33:56.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,差不多针尖大小
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.77,0:33:58.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它们很坚韧
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.50,0:34:02.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,节肢动物从所有的5次大灾难中幸存下来
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.81,0:34:05.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们存在了5亿年之久
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.57,0:34:07.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们一直认为生命很挑剔
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.94,0:34:09.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他只能接受
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.91,0:34:11.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不太冷 不太热
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.91,0:34:15.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不太暗 不咸 不酸 没辐射 的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.68,0:34:18.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有 不管怎么样 别忘了喝水
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.49,0:34:20.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们错了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.26,0:34:21.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}节肢动物证明我们错了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.59,0:34:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命可以承受人类绝对无法生存的环境
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.79,0:34:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命可以承受人类绝对无法生存的环境
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.03,0:34:28.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们和那些生活在最极端环境下的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.86,0:34:31.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们和那些生活在最极端环境下的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.43,0:34:34.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有少许的区别
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.44,0:34:36.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像一种语言中的不同方言
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.01,0:34:39.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球生命的遗传密码
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.71,0:34:47.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其他世界的生命又是什么样的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:50.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有着完全不同历史的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.32,0:34:53.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和我们完全不同的化学反应和进化过程
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.79,0:34:59.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想带你去一个遥远的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.36,0:35:01.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个和我们这个截然不同的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.80,0:35:05.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可能藏有生命
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.17,0:35:09.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果有 那绝对我们以前见过的都不同
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.07,0:35:11.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果有 那绝对我们以前见过的都不同
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.12,0:35:30.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,云雾完全包裹了泰坦（土卫六）的表面
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.52,0:35:32.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,土星的大月亮
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.52,0:35:35.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,泰坦和地球有点像
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.13,0:35:38.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它也有主要以氮气组成的大气层
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.63,0:35:40.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是比我们的稠密4倍
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:43.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,空气中没有丝毫氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.70,0:35:46.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比地球上任何地方都冷
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.20,0:35:49.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我依然想去那里
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.98,0:35:53.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们必须下降
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.51,0:35:55.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}几百公里的烟雾
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.98,0:35:58.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}才能看到它的表面
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.98,0:36:02.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是下面藏着我们熟悉的风景
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.23,0:36:13.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,泰坦是太阳系中除地球外唯一一个
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.70,0:36:15.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,下雨的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.17,0:36:18.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它有河流和海岸线
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.51,0:36:25.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有几百个湖泊
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.61,0:36:29.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有一个比北美的苏必利尔湖还大
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.18,0:36:31.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,蒸汽从湖面升起
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.18,0:36:33.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,凝结落下变成雨
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.42,0:36:37.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}雨落进河流
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.36,0:36:40.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}河流将山谷雕刻出风景
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.69,0:36:42.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像地球
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.96,0:36:47.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但有一个很大不同
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.07,0:36:49.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,泰坦上 海和雨不是由水组成
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.80,0:36:53.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是甲烷和乙烷
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.74,0:36:56.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在地球上 这些分子组成天然气
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.71,0:36:59.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在寒冷的泰坦上
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.58,0:37:01.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们是液态的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.89,0:37:08.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}泰坦上有很多水
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.92,0:37:11.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它们都冻的像石头一样硬
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.66,0:37:14.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上 这些风景和山脉
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.06,0:37:16.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是水做的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.56,0:37:18.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,零下几百度
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.80,0:37:22.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,泰坦冷的永远不会有液态的水
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.94,0:37:28.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}天体生物学家一直在猜想
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.17,0:37:31.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}泰坦上的碳氢化合物湖水中是否有生命
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.95,0:37:35.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种生命的化学成分
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.91,0:37:39.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一定和我们所知的都不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.35,0:37:42.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有的地球生命都需要水
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.19,0:37:44.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,泰坦的表面没有水
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.52,0:37:47.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我们可以想象另一种生命
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.09,0:37:49.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种生物可能呼吸氢气
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.69,0:37:51.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不是氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.20,0:37:54.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,呼出甲烷 而不是二氧化碳
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.70,0:37:58.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,乙炔可能是它们的能量来源 而不是糖
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.17,0:38:00.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们怎样才能找到它们
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.64,0:38:05.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果它们的帝国躲藏在这石油般的海水下
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.39,0:38:23.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们潜下克拉肯海
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.70,0:38:26.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是以北欧神话中的挪威海怪命名
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.07,0:38:32.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就算真有海怪在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.30,0:38:33.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们也看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.01,0:38:36.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太黑了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.58,0:38:40.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把地球上所有的石油和天然气加起来
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.01,0:38:44.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也只是泰坦储量的极小一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.25,0:38:50.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}让我们开点灯
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.49,0:38:57.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现在是表面下200米
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.20,0:39:03.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看到什么了吗
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.77,0:39:06.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那边 通道旁边
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.01,0:39:09.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也许我眼花了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.51,0:39:11.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们必须再来一次
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.51,0:39:14.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果我们想要确切知道
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.75,0:39:20.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想和你再说最后一个故事
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.42,0:39:24.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是最伟大的科学故事
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.93,0:39:32.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}关于我们世界上的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.82,0:39:57.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到40亿年前的地球
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.96,0:40:01.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有生命的星球
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.66,0:40:04.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没人知道生命如何诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.76,0:40:07.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,撞击和侵蚀摧毁了大部分的证据
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.17,0:40:09.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,撞击和侵蚀摧毁了大部分的证据
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.80,0:40:13.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学处在无知和已知之间
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.61,0:40:15.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们不怕承认我们不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.57,0:40:17.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一点也不丢人
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.91,0:40:21.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,丢人的是我们假装已经有了答案
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.78,0:40:23.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许观众中有人
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.48,0:40:25.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会成为首个解开这个谜题的人
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.02,0:40:28.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于地球生命的起源
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.99,0:40:37.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从现存的微生物得来的证据显示
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.86,0:40:39.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们最古老的祖先
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.80,0:40:41.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,喜欢高温
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.53,0:40:44.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球生命也许出现在热水中
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.47,0:40:46.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被水下的火山口环绕着
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.54,0:40:54.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在卡尔·萨根的宇宙节目中
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.05,0:40:56.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他找到了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.85,0:40:58.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从将近40亿年前的单细胞生物到你之间的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.95,0:41:01.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不间断的
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.52,0:41:03.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}线索
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.82,0:41:06.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}相当于40秒的40亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.99,0:41:10.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从不能分辨昼夜的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.56,0:41:14.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到可以探索宇宙的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.52,0:42:06.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是分子用40亿年时间进化的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.55,0:42:10.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是分子用40亿年时间进化的结果
